<h2>Knowledge Map — AI</h2>
<p>This page is a knowledge map that consolidates the <strong>structural knowledge index</strong> (<code>knowledge-index.json</code>) an AI built by reading <strong>every learning document under the AI World</strong>. It gathers each document's <strong>summary, key concepts, and related documents</strong> to show what lives where and <strong>how everything connects</strong>. The <strong>&ldquo;Related docs&rdquo;</strong> recommendations at the bottom of each document come from the same index, and you can explore these relations as a 3D graph — plus six 2D representations — in the <a href="#!cosmos"><strong>Knowledge Graph</strong></a>.</p>

<p>Knowledge in this wiki is organized in four levels: <strong>World → Domain → System → Document</strong> — <strong>World</strong> is a top-level knowledge world (AI · DOUZONE), <strong>Domain</strong> a knowledge area, <strong>System</strong> a concrete body of topics (the groups in the table below), and <strong>Document</strong> an individual page. This map covers the <strong>AI World</strong>; work knowledge is aggregated with the same structure by the <a href="#!dz-map"><strong>Douzone Knowledge Map</strong></a>.</p>

